   >> ğšŒğš•ğšŠğšœğšœ ğ™¼ğšŠğš’ğš— -->>
        :: Declares a class name as Main.
        :: In Java, every application must contain at least one class.

        :: Your class name is same as you save the name of file.
            For Example -
                  class Main - file name is Main
                  class Program - File name is Program.
        :: Always take the class name as File name.

  >> ğ™¼ğšŠğš’ğš— ğ™¼ğšğšğš‘ğš˜ğš -->>
      >< public static void main(String[] args) ><
      :: This line is the entry point of the program.
          
        :: public - Makes the method access from outside the class.
        :: static - Allows the method to be invoked without creating an instance of the class.
        :: void: Indicates that the method does not return a value.
        :: String[] args: Command-line arguments passed to the program.

